# =========================================================
# Najlepszy chomik w kadej dyscyplinie (discipline_id)
# ZAOENIE: winner_result to CZAS, zawsze mniejszy = lepszy
# =========================================================

# 1) Normalizacja wynikw w obrbie dyscypliny (z-score)
comp["z"] = comp.groupby("discipline_id")["winner_result"].transform(
    lambda s: (s - s.mean()) / (s.std(ddof=0) if s.std(ddof=0) > 0 else 1.0)
)

# 2) Score: im wikszy, tym lepiej -> odwracamy znak, bo mniejszy czas jest lepszy
comp["score"] = -comp["z"]

# 3) Ranking chomikw w kadej dyscyplinie
rank_disc = (
    comp
    .groupby(
        ["discipline_id", "name", "category", "hamster_id", "name_hamster"],
        as_index=False
    )
    .agg(
        wins=("competition_id", "count"),
        avg_score=("score", "mean"),
        best_time=("winner_result", "min"),      # najlepszy (najmniejszy) czas
        avg_time=("winner_result", "mean"),
        first_win=("competition_date", "min"),
        last_win=("competition_date", "max")
    )
)

# 4) Metryka czna: liczba zwycistw + jako wynikw (wins waniejsze)
rank_disc["combined"] = rank_disc["wins"] + 0.5 * rank_disc["avg_score"]

# 5) Najlepszy chomik dla kadej dyscypliny
best_by_discipline = (
    rank_disc
    .sort_values(["discipline_id", "combined"], ascending=[True, False])
    .groupby("discipline_id")
    .head(1)
    .sort_values("discipline_id")
)

# 6) Wynik kocowy (tabela do raportu)

        "name_hamster",

# =========================================================
# Ile trwa "szczyt kariery" u chomikw?
# Definicja: last_win - first_win (dla chomikw z >=2 zwycistwami)
# =========================================================

career = (
    comp.groupby(["hamster_id", "name_hamster"], as_index=False)
        .agg(
            wins=("competition_id", "count"),
            first_win=("competition_date", "min"),
            last_win=("competition_date", "max")
        )
)

career2 = career[career["wins"] >= 2].copy()
career2["peak_days"] = (career2["last_win"] - career2["first_win"]).dt.days
career2["peak_months"] = career2["peak_days"] / 30.44

print("Liczba chomikw z >=2 zwycistwami:", len(career2))
print("redni szczyt kariery:", round(career2["peak_days"].mean(), 1), "dni (",
      round(career2["peak_months"].mean(), 2), "mies.)")
print("Mediana szczytu kariery:", round(career2["peak_days"].median(), 1), "dni (",
      round(career2["peak_months"].median(), 2), "mies.)")
print("25%75%:", career2["peak_days"].quantile(0.25), "", career2["peak_days"].quantile(0.75), "dni")

# rozkad

# =========================================================
# Przewaga bogatych wacicieli: analiza per KATEGORIA i per DYSCYPLINA
# =========================================================

from scipy import stats
import numpy as np

def wealth_advantage_test(df, group_col):
    """
    df        - DataFrame (comp)
    group_col - 'category' lub 'discipline_id'
    Zwraca tabel z wynikami testu MannaWhitneya
    """
    results = []

    for g, sub in df.groupby(group_col):
        # kwartyle majtku
        q1 = sub["owner_networth"].quantile(0.25)
        q3 = sub["owner_networth"].quantile(0.75)

        bottom = sub[sub["owner_networth"] <= q1]["score"]
        top = sub[sub["owner_networth"] >= q3]["score"]

        if len(top) < 8 or len(bottom) < 8:
            results.append({
                group_col: g,
                "n_top": len(top),
                "n_bottom": len(bottom),
                "top_mean": np.nan,
                "bottom_mean": np.nan,
                "p_value": np.nan,
                "advantage": "za mao danych"
            })
            continue

        stat, p = stats.mannwhitneyu(top, bottom, alternative="two-sided")

        advantage = (
            "TAK (bogaci)" if (top.mean() > bottom.mean() and p < 0.05)
            else "TAK (biedni)" if (top.mean() < bottom.mean() and p < 0.05)
            else "NIE"
        )

        results.append({
            group_col: g,
            "n_top": len(top),
            "n_bottom": len(bottom),
            "top_mean": round(top.mean(), 3),
            "bottom_mean": round(bottom.mean(), 3),
            "p_value": round(p, 4),
            "advantage": advantage
        })

    return (
        pd.DataFrame(results)
        .sort_values("p_value", na_position="last")
        .reset_index(drop=True)
    )

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 1) Analiza per KATEGORIA
# ---------------------------------------------------------

adv_by_category = wealth_advantage_test(comp, "category")
adv_by_category

# =========================================================
# Rentowno federacji: przychody vs wydatki w czasie
# =========================================================

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# Wczytanie danych finansowych z bazy
funding_sources = pd.read_sql("SELECT * FROM funding_sources", conn)
sponsorships = pd.read_sql("SELECT * FROM sponsorships", conn)
employees = pd.read_sql("SELECT * FROM employees", conn)

# konwersja dat
for df in [funding_sources, sponsorships, employees]:
    for c in df.columns:
        if "date" in c:
            df[c] = pd.to_datetime(df[c])

# zakres lat analizy
year_min = comp["year"].min()
year_max = comp["year"].max()

# -------- PRZYCHODY --------

def expand_amounts_by_year(df, start_col, end_col, amount_col):
    rows = []
    for _, r in df.iterrows():
        start = r[start_col].year
        end = r[end_col].year if pd.notna(r[end_col]) else year_max
        for y in range(start, end + 1):
            if y >= year_min and y <= year_max:
                rows.append((y, float(r[amount_col])))
    return pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=["year", "amount"])

# dotacje
funding_y = (
    expand_amounts_by_year(funding_sources, "start_date", "end_date", "amount")
    .groupby("year", as_index=False)["amount"]
    .sum()
    .rename(columns={"amount": "funding"})
)

# sponsoring
sponsorship_y = (
    expand_amounts_by_year(sponsorships, "start_date", "end_date", "contribution_amount")
    .groupby("year", as_index=False)["amount"]
    .sum()
    .rename(columns={"amount": "sponsorship"})
)

# -------- WYDATKI (wynagrodzenia) --------

def payroll_by_year(employees, year_min, year_max):
    rows = []
    for y in range(year_min, year_max + 1):
        y_start = pd.Timestamp(y, 1, 1)
        y_end = pd.Timestamp(y, 12, 31)
        active = employees[
            (employees["start_date"] <= y_end) &
            ((employees["end_date"].isna()) | (employees["end_date"] >= y_start))
        ]
        rows.append((y, active["salary_amount"].sum() * 12))
    return pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=["year", "payroll"])

payroll_y = payroll_by_year(employees, year_min, year_max)

# -------- ZESTAWIENIE --------

finance = (
    pd.DataFrame({"year": range(year_min, year_max + 1)})
    .merge(funding_y, on="year", how="left")
    .merge(sponsorship_y, on="year", how="left")
    .merge(payroll_y, on="year", how="left")
    .fillna(0)
)

finance["income"] = finance["funding"] + finance["sponsorship"]
finance["expenses"] = finance["payroll"]
finance["balance"] = finance["income"] - finance["expenses"]

finance
plt.figure()
plt.plot(finance["year"], finance["income"], marker="o", label="Przychody")
plt.plot(finance["year"], finance["expenses"], marker="o", label="Wydatki")
plt.legend()
plt.title("Przychody i wydatki federacji w czasie")
plt.xlabel("Rok")
plt.ylabel("PLN")
plt.show()

# =========================================================
# P3 (POPRAWIONE): Czy liczba POTENCJALNYCH startw wpywa na wyniki?
# =========================================================

from scipy import stats
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# zakres dat zawodw (globalny)
min_comp_date = comp["competition_date"].min()
max_comp_date = comp["competition_date"].max()

# 1) Wyznaczenie okresu kariery kadego chomika
ham_career = hamsters.copy()
ham_career["career_start"] = ham_career["birth_date"] + pd.Timedelta(days=60)
ham_career["career_end"] = ham_career["retire_date"].fillna(max_comp_date)

# zabezpieczenie: nie wykraczamy poza dane
ham_career["career_start"] = ham_career["career_start"].clip(lower=min_comp_date)
ham_career["career_end"] = ham_career["career_end"].clip(upper=max_comp_date)

# 2) Liczba POTENCJALNYCH startw = liczba zawodw w okresie kariery
def count_possible_starts(row):
    return comp[
        (comp["competition_date"] >= row["career_start"]) &
        (comp["competition_date"] <= row["career_end"])
    ]["competition_id"].nunique()

ham_career["possible_starts"] = ham_career.apply(count_possible_starts, axis=1)

# 3) Wyniki sportowe chomika
perf = (
    comp.groupby(["hamster_id", "name_hamster"], as_index=False)
        .agg(
            avg_score=("score", "mean"),
            wins=("competition_id", "count")
        )
)

# 4) Poczenie: potencjalne starty + wyniki
analysis_p3 = ham_career.merge(
    perf, on="hamster_id", how="left"
).dropna(subset=["avg_score"])

analysis_p3[["name_hamster", "possible_starts", "avg_score"]].head()
# 5) Korelacja: potencjalne starty  wynik
rho, p = stats.spearmanr(
    analysis_p3["possible_starts"],
    analysis_p3["avg_score"]
)

print(f"Spearman(possible_starts, avg_score): rho={rho:.3f}, p={p:.4f}")
# 6) Wizualizacja
plt.figure()
plt.scatter(
    analysis_p3["possible_starts"],
    analysis_p3["avg_score"],
    alpha=0.6
)
plt.xlabel("Liczba potencjalnych startw (zawody w okresie kariery)")
plt.ylabel("redni wynik (score)")
plt.title("Potencjalne starty a wyniki chomikw")
plt.show()

Spearman(possible_starts, avg_score): rho=0.063, p=0.6556

# P4 (POPRAWIONE): Konkurencyjno dyscyplin
# Znormalizowane odchylenie: std / mean (CV)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

competitiveness = (
    comp.groupby(["discipline_id", "name"], as_index=False)
        .agg(
            events=("competition_id", "count"),
            mean_time=("winner_result", "mean"),
            std_time=("winner_result", "std")
        )
)

# wspczynnik zmiennoci (CV)
competitiveness["cv"] = competitiveness["std_time"] / competitiveness["mean_time"]

competitiveness = competitiveness.sort_values("cv")

competitiveness
# Wizualizacja konkurencyjnoci
plt.figure()
plt.barh(competitiveness["name"], competitiveness["cv"])
plt.xlabel("Wspczynnik zmiennoci (std / mean)")
plt.title("Konkurencyjno dyscyplin (niszy = bardziej wyrwnana)")
plt.show()
